create_material:
Create a material described by the following intent:

{{intent}}

Output a JSON object using only the tag-based schema: { 'type': 'material', 'name': string, 'tags': ['sand'|'flow'|'float'|'static'], 'density': number, 'color': string|[r,g,b], 'reactions'?: [ { with: string, result: string, byproduct?: string, probability?: number, priority?: number } ], 'condense'?: { at: 'top', result: string, probability?: number } }.

Examples:
Sand+Water => {"type":"material","name":"Silt","tags":["sand"],"density":1.3,"color":[150,140,120],"description":"Fine damp grit."}
Fire+Sand => {"type":"material","name":"Glass","tags":["static"],"density":2.4,"color":[190,200,210],"description":"Clear brittle solid."}
Water+Oil => {"type":"material","name":"Emulsion","tags":["flow"],"density":0.9,"color":[220,210,180],"description":"Cloudy liquid blend."}
Steam+Air => {"type":"material","name":"Mist","tags":["float"],"density":0.2,"color":[200,200,220],"description":"Light drifting vapor."}
Salt+Water => {"type":"material","name":"Saltwater","tags":["flow"],"density":1.1,"color":[120,150,200],"description":"Briny liquid."}
Metal+Fire => {"type":"material","name":"MoltenMetal","tags":["flow"],"density":3.5,"color":[220,120,60],"description":"Hot viscous metal."}
Stone+Air => {"type":"material","name":"Dust","tags":["sand"],"density":0.6,"color":[180,170,160],"description":"Fine granular powder."}
Wood+Fire => {"type":"material","name":"Char","tags":["static"],"density":1.2,"color":[40,40,40],"description":"Brittle black solid."}

The JSON must be valid. Do not include primitives, budgets, code blocks, or extra text.
